Prologue: Pottawatomie Massacre, 5-24-56 (Saturday night)




Characters:
  1. US marshal or deputy marshal
     T.W. Hays (who was with Pate historically)
     (Fain (from Lecompton with Sumner historically, sent by Shannon)?)
  2. Henry Clay Pate and his Westport Sharpshooters
  3. John Brown and his company
  4. Sumner or Stuart, and the First Dragoons
  5. abolitionist circuit preacher (Lovejoy?)
  6. his daughter (?)
  9. residents of Black Jack
  10. residents of Palmyra
  11. residents of Prairie City
    (James E. Carpenter and the Jones brothers inter alia)
  
  Cantrel: Missouri free-stater, executed by Whitfield/Pate on 6/6/56
  Lt. J.R. Church: his men encountered Brown on 5/25/56, got them to disperse
  
Three little towns:
  Black Jack in the east, pro-slavery
    (Pate's camp: "3/4 mi west of town, near edge of prairie")
  Palmyra in the north, nw of BJ, abolition ("four or five families")
  Prairie City in the southwest, free soil ("neighboring hamlet")
  Hickory Point near Palmyra, i.e. Palmyra at S end of H.P.
  St. Bernard, "five miles from camp" i.e. Black Jack
  Brown's forces camp at Ottawa Creek
  Bull Creek: 12 mi. E of Palmyra
  California road runs south from Palmyra to Dutch Henry's


